sinit: sinit (suckless init)
sinit:  
sinit: sinit is a simple init. It was initially based on Rich Felker's minimal
sinit: init. There are 3 signals that sinit will act on:
sinit: SIGUSR1: powers off the machine
sinit: SIGINT:  reboots the machine
sinit: SIGCHLD: reap children
sinit: 
sinit: The default initialization script is /etc/rc.d/rc.start
sinit: The default reboot/poweroff script is /etc/rc.d/rc.stop
sinit: 
sinit:  
